1
00:00:09,053 --> 00:00:09,849
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,194 --> 00:00:18,822
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,864 --> 00:00:22,025
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,701 --> 00:00:26,363
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,471 --> 00:00:30,099
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,809 --> 00:00:34,903
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,413 --> 00:00:38,678
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,151 --> 00:00:44,417
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,058 --> 00:00:48,923
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:49,026 --> 00:00:50,755
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,828 --> 00:00:53,160
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,699 --> 00:00:56,462
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,534 --> 00:00:58,434
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,502 --> 00:01:00,936
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:09,404
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,381 --> 00:01:13,009
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,451 --> 00:01:16,648
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,392 --> 00:01:22,689
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,263 --> 00:01:26,787
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:37,586 --> 00:01:40,282
<i>It seems I've overused</i>
<i>my Sharingan...</i>

21
00:01:41,990 --> 00:01:43,890
Are you alright, Sensei?

22
00:01:44,359 --> 00:01:48,489
Not really... It will be hard just to
move for about a week...

23
00:01:49,164 --> 00:01:49,926
Well...

24
00:01:49,998 --> 00:01:52,694
It would be better if
you didn't move for a while.

25
00:01:53,101 --> 00:01:53,999
O-Okay...

26
00:01:58,406 --> 00:02:00,567
Hey! Sensei's awake.

27
00:02:01,209 --> 00:02:02,437
Come on!

28
00:02:02,978 --> 00:02:04,445
Your Sharingan is fantastic,

29
00:02:04,579 --> 00:02:08,037
but if it puts that much of a strain
on your body, it may not be worth it!

30
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:09,510
S-Sorry...

31
00:02:10,118 --> 00:02:11,346
But you know...

32
00:02:11,586 --> 00:02:14,214
He did take down
a real powerful Ninja like that!

33
00:02:14,289 --> 00:02:16,018
We probably don't need to
worry for a while.

34
00:02:16,591 --> 00:02:20,652
Anyway, that kid with the mask...
What was he?

35
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:23,894
He was an ANBU black ops
from the Hidden Mist village.

36
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:27,065
It's a mask that the elite
Ninja Tracking Unit wears.

37
00:02:28,103 --> 00:02:29,297
The elite Ninja Tracking Unit?

38
00:02:29,704 --> 00:02:32,332
They're commonly called the
"fire extinguishing corps,"

39
00:02:33,108 --> 00:02:36,874
and their duty is to erase all traces
that a Ninja ever lived.

40
00:02:37,679 --> 00:02:39,203
The body of the Ninja reveals
a variety of things...

41
00:02:39,281 --> 00:02:44,014
Ninjutsu secrets and Chakra characteristics
which permeate the Ninja of their village...

42
00:02:44,085 --> 00:02:48,988
the composition of secret medicines
used on a Ninja's body...

43
00:02:50,825 --> 00:02:52,588
For instance, if I were to die,

44
00:02:53,361 --> 00:02:56,228
every secret about my Sharingan
would be investigated thoroughly,

45
00:02:57,399 --> 00:02:58,661
and in the worst case,

46
00:02:58,733 --> 00:03:01,827
there's a danger that
my entire Jutsu could be stolen.

47
00:03:02,837 --> 00:03:04,270
In other words,
Tracker Ninja are specialists

48
00:03:04,339 --> 00:03:07,365
that prevent village secrets
from leaking out

49
00:03:07,809 --> 00:03:10,676
by killing Rogue Ninja
who've run away from their village,

50
00:03:10,745 --> 00:03:15,114
and completely eliminating
their bodies.

51
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:20,916
First, I'll cut the mouth cloth
and have him spit up blood...

52
00:03:23,992 --> 00:03:24,981
It's alright.

53
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,755
I'll do it... myself...

54
00:03:28,263 --> 00:03:31,323
What?
You've already come back to life...

55
00:03:35,904 --> 00:03:39,465
Darn, you really are rough...

56
00:03:41,242 --> 00:03:42,402
You too, Zabuza.

57
00:03:42,577 --> 00:03:46,343
Please don't pull them out
so violently or you really will die.

58
00:03:51,386 --> 00:03:54,378
How long do you plan on keeping
that shady-looking mask on?!

59
00:03:54,589 --> 00:03:55,385
Take it off!

60
00:03:56,191 --> 00:04:01,652
It's a relic from the past,
and it's been handy for trickery...

61
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:10,268
But if I hadn't rescued you,
you certainly would have been killed.

62
00:04:10,839 --> 00:04:12,739
If you were going to put me
into a state of apparent death,

63
00:04:12,807 --> 00:04:15,640
you didn't need to aim for
the secret opening on my neck.

64
00:04:16,277 --> 00:04:19,610
You're really a nasty one.

65
00:04:20,315 --> 00:04:21,907
It couldn't be helped...

66
00:04:22,851 --> 00:04:27,049
Besides, I didn't want to mark up
your immaculate body.

67
00:04:27,922 --> 00:04:31,517
And also, I can aim more accurately
on the point on the neck

68
00:04:31,593 --> 00:04:33,561
where there's not much muscle.

69
00:04:36,798 --> 00:04:39,358
You'll be numb for about a week
and won't be able to move.

70
00:04:40,001 --> 00:04:44,700
But since you're Zabuza,
perhaps you'll soon be able to move...

71
00:04:48,042 --> 00:04:51,944
You're so innocent, smart,
and untainted...

72
00:04:52,814 --> 00:04:55,009
That's what I like about you.

73
00:04:56,918 --> 00:04:59,250
I am, after all, still a child.

74
00:05:02,023 --> 00:05:03,285
The fog has lifted.

75
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:04,216
Yes.

76
00:05:06,428 --> 00:05:08,487
Will you be alright the next time?

77
00:05:09,898 --> 00:05:10,592
The next time...

78
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,825
I'll be able to see right
through the Sharingan.

79
00:05:14,202 --> 00:05:20,163
<i>The Forest of Chakra</i>

80
00:05:22,410 --> 00:05:23,206
<i>What is this?</i>

81
00:05:23,978 --> 00:05:25,707
<i>Even though Zabuza is dead...</i>

82
00:05:25,914 --> 00:05:27,882
<i>this indescribable uneasiness...</i>

83
00:05:28,850 --> 00:05:30,215
<i>it must mean something</i>
<i>very important...</i>

84
00:05:31,886 --> 00:05:34,320
<i>I have a feeling</i>
<i>I've overlooked something.</i>

85
00:05:35,223 --> 00:05:37,783
What's going on?!
Sensei?

86
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:38,784
What?

87
00:05:38,860 --> 00:05:41,454
Oh... so to continue my earlier story...

88
00:05:42,797 --> 00:05:43,786
Ninja trackers...

89
00:05:43,865 --> 00:05:47,357
take care of the bodies of people they've
killed, immediately and on the spot.

90
00:05:47,969 --> 00:05:49,459
So what about that?

91
00:05:50,638 --> 00:05:54,039
What did that kid with
the mask do with Zabuza?

92
00:05:57,011 --> 00:05:58,444
How should we know?!

93
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:01,308
That masked one
took Zabuza away!

94
00:06:02,550 --> 00:06:03,209
That's right...

95
00:06:04,552 --> 00:06:08,579
If he needed proof he'd killed Zabuza,
he could simply have taken the head...

96
00:06:09,824 --> 00:06:10,916
And the question is...

97
00:06:10,992 --> 00:06:15,088
the weapon the Ninja tracker kid
used to kill Zabuza...

98
00:06:16,764 --> 00:06:17,696
A regular Senbon...

99
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:19,799
That's impossible...

100
00:06:20,235 --> 00:06:22,863
Right... it's impossible?!

101
00:06:24,806 --> 00:06:27,900
What have you guys
been clamoring on and on about?!

102
00:06:29,143 --> 00:06:31,839
It's probably that...
Zabuza is alive!

103
00:06:34,115 --> 00:06:34,672
What?

104
00:06:35,383 --> 00:06:37,317
What the heck do you mean?!

105
00:06:37,385 --> 00:06:40,877
But Kakashi Sensei,
you made sure that he was dead!

106
00:06:41,523 --> 00:06:43,218
It's true, I did make sure...

107
00:06:44,192 --> 00:06:48,026
But, he was probably just in
a state of near-death.

108
00:06:52,734 --> 00:06:57,569
The Senbon that Tracker Ninja used has
a very low ability to kill

109
00:06:57,639 --> 00:06:59,903
unless it hits a vital spot...

110
00:07:00,808 --> 00:07:03,402
It's something that was originally used
for medical treatments

111
00:07:03,478 --> 00:07:04,945
such as acupuncture therapy.

112
00:07:06,014 --> 00:07:09,450
Ninja trackers know all about
the structure of the human body...

113
00:07:10,251 --> 00:07:14,210
putting people into a state of apparent
near death is probably simple for them.

114
00:07:15,456 --> 00:07:18,653
First, he went to the trouble of
taking Zabuza's corpse

115
00:07:18,726 --> 00:07:20,751
which was probably heavier
than he is.

116
00:07:21,996 --> 00:07:26,365
Second, he used a Senbon,
a weapon with a low ability to kill.

117
00:07:28,002 --> 00:07:29,264
From these two factors,

118
00:07:29,337 --> 00:07:34,240
that youth wasn't aiming to
kill Zabuza but to save him.

119
00:07:35,610 --> 00:07:37,669
Aren't you reading
way too much into it?

120
00:07:38,179 --> 00:07:38,838
No...

121
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:43,376
If something seems fishy,
make preparations before it's too late.

122
00:07:43,851 --> 00:07:45,716
That's also an iron clad rule
of the Shinobi!

123
00:07:51,659 --> 00:07:56,653
<i>Humph... To hear that Zabuza</i>
<i>may be alive and to be pleased...</i>

124
00:07:57,165 --> 00:08:00,293
Sensei, what do we do to make preparations
before it's too late?

125
00:08:01,069 --> 00:08:02,559
You won't even be able
to move for a while...

126
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:08,265
I'll assign you training!

127
00:08:08,843 --> 00:08:13,712
W-Wait a minute! Even with training,
we're not gonna be that strong!

128
00:08:14,082 --> 00:08:18,781
Our opponent is a Ninja whom even you,
with the Sharingan, had a tough fight with!

129
00:08:18,853 --> 00:08:21,651
Are you trying to kill us?!

130
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:23,357
Sakura...

131
00:08:23,625 --> 00:08:26,458
Who was it that saved me
during my difficult battle?

132
00:08:27,295 --> 00:08:30,992
You've all quickly grown...
especially Naruto!

133
00:08:33,101 --> 00:08:34,898
You've grown the most!

134
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:42,401
<i>He clearly does seem somewhat</i>
<i>stronger than before, but...</i>

135
00:08:43,277 --> 00:08:47,976
So you noticed, Kakashi Sensei!
Now it's getting interesting!

136
00:08:48,449 --> 00:08:50,041
It's not interesting at all...

137
00:08:56,257 --> 00:08:57,246
Who the heck are you?

138
00:08:57,825 --> 00:09:00,316
Hey, Inari!
Where've you been?!

139
00:09:00,395 --> 00:09:02,090
Welcome back... Grandpa...

140
00:09:02,764 --> 00:09:04,925
Inari, what sort of greeting is that?!

141
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:08,125
These are the Ninja
who escorted your grandpa!

142
00:09:08,703 --> 00:09:11,069
It's okay, it's okay.
Right, Inari?

143
00:09:17,679 --> 00:09:19,613
Mom, these guys will die...

144
00:09:19,914 --> 00:09:22,849
There's no way they can
oppose Gato and win.

145
00:09:22,917 --> 00:09:24,885
Say what, you little brat!

146
00:09:25,253 --> 00:09:27,118
Now listen up!

147
00:09:27,188 --> 00:09:29,850
I'm a super hero who's gonna become
an awesome Ninja

148
00:09:29,924 --> 00:09:31,152
named Hokage in the future!

149
00:09:31,225 --> 00:09:33,659
I don't know if it's Gato or
Chocolat or whatever...

150
00:09:33,728 --> 00:09:36,288
I'm not worried
about those guys, at all!

151
00:09:36,531 --> 00:09:41,468
Huh, a hero. That's ridiculous!
There's no such thing!

152
00:09:41,803 --> 00:09:43,828
W-What did you say?!

153
00:09:44,238 --> 00:09:45,227
Stop that!

154
00:09:45,907 --> 00:09:48,899
If you don't want to die,
you'd better hurry up and go home...

155
00:09:52,580 --> 00:09:54,411
Inari, where're you going?

156
00:09:56,317 --> 00:09:58,285
The sea...
I'll be looking at the sea...

157
00:10:03,458 --> 00:10:04,550
I apologize.

158
00:10:08,096 --> 00:10:08,687
Shucks!

159
00:10:09,731 --> 00:10:13,223
That brat... I need to tell him
a thing or two!

160
00:10:18,873 --> 00:10:19,430
Huh?

161
00:10:21,275 --> 00:10:22,333
<i>Is he crying?!</i>

162
00:10:35,723 --> 00:10:37,088
D-Dad...

163
00:10:48,837 --> 00:10:51,431
So, now the training begins!

164
00:10:51,773 --> 00:10:52,296
Yes, sir!

165
00:10:52,974 --> 00:10:59,709
So... before that, let me again explain
Chakra power for a Ninja, from the basics.

166
00:11:00,048 --> 00:11:00,912
At this point...

167
00:11:01,416 --> 00:11:05,113
Of course we know about that!
Chatora, right?

168
00:11:05,854 --> 00:11:06,843
It's Chakra...

169
00:11:07,856 --> 00:11:09,551
Yes, Sakura...?

170
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:11,224
Are you listening, Naruto?!

171
00:11:11,559 --> 00:11:13,789
It's tiresome, so I'll explain it simply!

172
00:11:15,964 --> 00:11:21,231
Chakra is energy that
a Ninja needs when he uses a Jutsu!

173
00:11:21,936 --> 00:11:23,699
It's made up of two energies:

174
00:11:23,772 --> 00:11:28,334
1) Physical energy gathered together
from each and every cell in the body and

175
00:11:28,743 --> 00:11:35,012
2) Spiritual energy accumulated based
on numerous trainings and experiences!

176
00:11:35,583 --> 00:11:40,145
In other words, Jutsu wrings out and
combines these two energies

177
00:11:40,221 --> 00:11:41,518
from within the body,

178
00:11:41,589 --> 00:11:44,717
and this is called
"combining the Chakra."

179
00:11:44,993 --> 00:11:50,192
Then Chakra is activated
by forming hand "signs."

180
00:11:51,266 --> 00:11:52,358
That's exactly right!

181
00:11:52,634 --> 00:11:55,967
Iruka Sensei really does
have good students.

182
00:11:57,539 --> 00:12:01,532
Whatever! I may not understand
difficult explanations,

183
00:12:01,676 --> 00:12:03,576
but I'll just learn it with my body!

184
00:12:03,912 --> 00:12:05,311
Naruto is absolutely right...

185
00:12:05,847 --> 00:12:08,509
We're already able to use Jutsu...

186
00:12:08,683 --> 00:12:12,779
No! All of you still haven't used
Chakra efficiently.

187
00:12:13,154 --> 00:12:13,882
What?!

188
00:12:14,956 --> 00:12:16,287
Hold on and listen...

189
00:12:16,825 --> 00:12:18,588
As Sakura explained earlier,

190
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:23,697
combining Chakra means picking up
both the physical and spiritual energies

191
00:12:23,765 --> 00:12:25,630
and mixing them together
within the body.

192
00:12:27,435 --> 00:12:32,498
And of course the amount of each energy,
the preparation of the energy,

193
00:12:32,574 --> 00:12:35,099
changes based on
the Jutsu you want to activate...

194
00:12:35,743 --> 00:12:38,940
All of you at present aren't
using Chakra efficiently!

195
00:12:40,181 --> 00:12:43,275
Even if you're able to combine
a lot of Chakra,

196
00:12:43,818 --> 00:12:46,218
if you're not able to control it
in a balanced way

197
00:12:46,788 --> 00:12:49,586
the effectiveness of the Jutsu
not only will be cut in half

198
00:12:50,024 --> 00:12:51,992
but it may not even
be activated at all.

199
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:56,257
Wasting energy will prevent you from
battling for long periods.

200
00:12:56,331 --> 00:12:58,856
These are some of
the weaknesses that can occur.

201
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:01,662
W-What should we do...?

202
00:13:03,404 --> 00:13:05,702
You need to learn to control
the Chakra with your body!

203
00:13:05,907 --> 00:13:10,503
It's difficult training that requires you
to put your life on the line to master!

204
00:13:12,714 --> 00:13:14,113
W-What will we do?

205
00:13:15,216 --> 00:13:16,148
Hm?

206
00:13:17,185 --> 00:13:17,844
Tree climbing...

207
00:13:18,286 --> 00:13:19,651
Tree climbing?!

208
00:13:19,954 --> 00:13:20,818
That's right.

209
00:13:21,055 --> 00:13:23,182
But it's not just simple tree-climbing!

210
00:13:23,758 --> 00:13:25,521
You will climb
without using your hands.

211
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,384
What? How?

212
00:13:29,531 --> 00:13:31,522
Well! Just watch.

213
00:13:47,649 --> 00:13:48,775
He's climbing...

214
00:13:49,484 --> 00:13:52,078
Perpendicular to the tree
and with his feet!

215
00:13:55,323 --> 00:13:57,348
So see, kind of like this...

216
00:13:58,026 --> 00:14:01,621
Focus the Chakra on the bottoms of your feet
and make them stick to the tree trunk.

217
00:14:02,363 --> 00:14:05,093
If you use Chakra well,
you can do things like this.

218
00:14:05,366 --> 00:14:06,355
Wait a minute!

219
00:14:06,801 --> 00:14:09,326
How does something like that
make you strong?

220
00:14:09,771 --> 00:14:11,796
So this is the main point...

221
00:14:12,407 --> 00:14:14,466
The aim of this training is
to accumulate

222
00:14:14,542 --> 00:14:18,171
the required amount of combined Chakra
to the required spot...

223
00:14:18,980 --> 00:14:22,074
This is surprisingly difficult
even for an expert Ninja.

224
00:14:22,917 --> 00:14:25,977
The amount of Chakra used
for tree climbing is very subtle.

225
00:14:27,188 --> 00:14:32,023
And the bottoms of the feet are
the most difficult place to gather Chakra.

226
00:14:32,927 --> 00:14:36,158
Anyway! In other words,
if you master that control

227
00:14:36,731 --> 00:14:41,634
it will be possible to master
any Jutsu. In theory, that is!

228
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:46,135
The second aim is to maintain
that combined Chakra.

229
00:14:46,975 --> 00:14:50,103
Ninja combine the most Chakra
during battles.

230
00:14:50,878 --> 00:14:52,277
Under such situations,

231
00:14:52,347 --> 00:14:56,010
"control" and "maintenance"
of Chakra becomes most difficult.

232
00:14:57,051 --> 00:15:01,283
So anyway, nothing's really gonna
happen with me saying this and that...

233
00:15:02,323 --> 00:15:05,190
You'll need to learn it with your bodies

234
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:11,530
Use that Kunai to put a mark
at the spot

235
00:15:11,599 --> 00:15:14,329
where you can climb up to
under your own strength now.

236
00:15:15,970 --> 00:15:20,134
Next make an effort to
put a mark further from it.

237
00:15:21,676 --> 00:15:24,474
You aren't good enough to
walk up from the start,

238
00:15:25,079 --> 00:15:29,607
so run and use your momentum
to get used to it... You got it?!

239
00:15:31,819 --> 00:15:35,880
This training is nothing!
Hah, it's too easy for me!

240
00:15:36,824 --> 00:15:40,089
After all, I'm the man
who's grown the most!

241
00:15:40,428 --> 00:15:44,023
Enough with the talk...
Now get to it. Try climbing any tree.

242
00:15:46,367 --> 00:15:49,928
<i>OK, so first I need to gather</i>
<i>the Chakra on the bottoms of my feet...</i>

243
00:15:58,112 --> 00:16:02,344
Ready!! Here I go!

244
00:16:18,499 --> 00:16:21,957
<i>I didn't think it'd be this difficult to</i>
<i>maintain a constant amount of Chakra...</i>

245
00:16:22,270 --> 00:16:24,261
<i>If the Chakra is too strong</i>
<i>you get pushed back...</i>

246
00:16:26,574 --> 00:16:30,977
<i>But if the Chakra is too weak,</i>
<i>there's no sticking power and that happens.</i>

247
00:16:33,614 --> 00:16:34,171
Well...!

248
00:16:34,348 --> 00:16:36,873
The difference between Naruto and Sasuke
seems about right.

249
00:16:37,285 --> 00:16:38,650
This is pretty easy!

250
00:16:39,587 --> 00:16:40,053
What?!

251
00:16:41,389 --> 00:16:42,822
S-Sakura!

252
00:16:46,894 --> 00:16:53,163
So, it looks like the one with the best control
of the Chakra is Sakura, the girl...

253
00:16:57,271 --> 00:16:59,136
Wow! Way to go, Sakura!

254
00:16:59,207 --> 00:17:01,334
Just what you'd expect from
the girl I set my sights on!

255
00:17:01,609 --> 00:17:03,304
<i>But it does sort of tick me off!</i>

256
00:17:04,178 --> 00:17:04,667
Whatever!

257
00:17:05,012 --> 00:17:07,640
<i>I wanted Sasuke to notice me...</i>

258
00:17:07,982 --> 00:17:10,143
<i>Why does this always happen?!</i>

259
00:17:10,585 --> 00:17:13,247
Well, not only does Sakura have
knowledge about Chakra,

260
00:17:13,454 --> 00:17:16,446
her control and stamina
are pretty good.

261
00:17:16,891 --> 00:17:18,017
It looks like...

262
00:17:18,259 --> 00:17:23,697
She might be the closest one to
becoming a Hokage... unlike someone else.

263
00:17:24,165 --> 00:17:28,192
And also, the Uchiha Clan
isn't really that great...

264
00:17:28,569 --> 00:17:30,298
Shut up Sensei!

265
00:17:31,472 --> 00:17:33,303
<i>Sasuke won't like me then!</i>

266
00:17:37,078 --> 00:17:39,911
<i>Having said that... Naruto and Sasuke...</i>

267
00:17:39,981 --> 00:17:43,382
<i>Those two have an incredible amount</i>
<i>of Chakra hidden in them...</i>

268
00:17:43,451 --> 00:17:44,577
<i>that Sakura can't even match!</i>

269
00:17:45,319 --> 00:17:49,380
<i>If this training goes well,</i>
<i>this will become an asset to them...</i>

270
00:17:49,891 --> 00:17:53,019
OK! First I'll catch up to Sasuke!

271
00:17:53,327 --> 00:17:54,555
I'll do it... for sure!

272
00:18:00,268 --> 00:18:00,700
<i>Whatever!</i>

273
00:18:02,370 --> 00:18:04,600
<i>Even if they do that,</i>
<i>it's just a waste...</i>

274
00:18:27,195 --> 00:18:28,389
Unbelievable...

275
00:18:28,563 --> 00:18:30,554
Even you got beaten and
had to come back?

276
00:18:30,731 --> 00:18:33,359
The Ninja from the Hidden Mist Village
look like total weaklings!

277
00:18:33,768 --> 00:18:35,736
You can't even clean up after
your subordinates,

278
00:18:35,803 --> 00:18:38,033
and you think you're a "demon"!
Don't make me laugh!

279
00:18:45,746 --> 00:18:46,838
<i>So they're drawing swords...</i>

280
00:18:49,083 --> 00:18:50,243
Hold on. Wait.

281
00:18:50,952 --> 00:18:53,944
Hey... There's no need to stay silent!

282
00:18:54,889 --> 00:18:57,221
Why don't you say something?

283
00:19:01,529 --> 00:19:03,861
Don't touch Zabuza
with your dirty hands!

284
00:19:04,866 --> 00:19:06,356
I-It's gonna break...!

285
00:19:11,706 --> 00:19:13,230
<i>N-No way...</i>

286
00:19:13,975 --> 00:19:15,567
<i>He moved...in an instant...</i>

287
00:19:16,210 --> 00:19:20,169
I wouldn't do that...
I'm ticked off!!

288
00:19:23,918 --> 00:19:24,509
Next time...

289
00:19:24,685 --> 00:19:26,983
If you lose again next time...

290
00:19:27,054 --> 00:19:29,545
remember that there'll be
no place for you here!

291
00:19:31,225 --> 00:19:32,021
I'm leaving!

292
00:19:36,831 --> 00:19:39,265
Haku... Such unnecessary actions...

293
00:19:40,067 --> 00:19:41,056
I know...

294
00:19:42,637 --> 00:19:46,198
But it's too early to take down
Gato right now...

295
00:19:46,841 --> 00:19:48,604
If we make trouble here...

296
00:19:51,212 --> 00:19:54,147
We'll be pursued by them again.

297
00:19:54,815 --> 00:19:56,715
We must restrain ourselves for now.

298
00:19:58,953 --> 00:19:59,749
Yeah...

299
00:20:00,421 --> 00:20:01,547
You're right.

300
00:20:07,628 --> 00:20:09,687
Ohhhhh...

301
00:20:11,499 --> 00:20:12,227
Ou-ch!!

302
00:20:21,776 --> 00:20:23,175
<i>I'm totally worn out!</i>

303
00:20:23,544 --> 00:20:25,705
<i>How much stamina</i>
<i>can those two have?</i>

304
00:20:32,119 --> 00:20:35,680
<i>But Naruto isn't getting</i>
<i>any better at all.</i>

305
00:20:36,457 --> 00:20:38,857
<i>He'll soon give up and</i>
<i>start throwing a tantrum.</i>

306
00:20:41,295 --> 00:20:41,852
Shoot!

307
00:20:42,129 --> 00:20:45,530
<i>See! He sure is</i>
<i>an easy one to figure out!</i>

308
00:20:47,068 --> 00:20:48,501
Hey, Sakura!

309
00:20:49,003 --> 00:20:50,766
Can you give me some tips?

310
00:20:51,238 --> 00:20:51,602
What?

311
00:20:52,573 --> 00:20:54,541
Let's keep it a secret from Sasuke!
Come on, come on.

312
00:20:57,745 --> 00:21:02,273
He's getting stronger and stronger...
How strong will he get?

313
00:21:03,117 --> 00:21:04,209
At any rate Naruto...

314
00:21:04,819 --> 00:21:09,017
the amount of your dormant Chakra
is probably more than Sasuke's.

315
00:21:11,192 --> 00:21:14,457
And it's even more than mine!

316
00:21:15,162 --> 00:21:17,858
I look forward to it... I really do.

317
00:22:54,431 --> 00:22:57,491
That Inari...
He was crying all by himself.

318
00:22:58,101 --> 00:23:00,035
He was looking at the sea
and crying the entire time.

319
00:23:01,138 --> 00:23:04,539
He's always crying all alone.

320
00:23:05,108 --> 00:23:06,632
What's that gonna do?

321
00:23:07,344 --> 00:23:09,972
What happened
that made him so sad?!

322
00:23:11,381 --> 00:23:14,077
Next time:
"The Land Where a Hero Once Lived"
